@* Checkbox two-way binding (BENCH n°26): @bind="on" on a checkbox <input>. `on` is a BOOL signal --
   read by the #status class ternary (a faithful string, unlike a raw @on which would render "false"
   vs C#'s "False") AND assigned by @bind + Set. The checkbox's .checked property is the two-way surface
   (already a bool, no BindConverter parsing). #set flips it programmatically; clicking the box flips the
   field. *@

<input id="box" type="checkbox" @bind="on" />

<span id="status" class="@(on ? "on" : "off")">status</span>

<button id="set" @onclick="Set">Set</button>

@code {
    private bool on = false;

    private void Set()
    {
        on = true;
    }
}
